02:32.261 --> 02:35.263
[breathing heavily]

02:38.868 --> 02:40.802
[groans]

02:43.239 --> 02:45.268
Isn't that Rahm's spy?

02:46.876 --> 02:48.042
(Bebe)
So it is.

02:48.077 --> 02:50.111
Too bad it had to end like this.

02:50.146 --> 02:51.780
Come on.

02:54.553 --> 02:57.418
Targets have entered
the NeedWant.

02:57.453 --> 02:59.821
Is the sphere online?

02:59.855 --> 03:01.156
Fully operational.

03:04.393 --> 03:05.393
Well, let's do this.

03:05.427 --> 03:08.396
[dramatic music]

03:08.430 --> 03:16.437
♪ ♪

03:17.910 --> 03:19.240
He was brave in the end.

03:19.275 --> 03:22.143
Datak Tarr?
[scoffs]

03:22.178 --> 03:25.847
Yeah, well, he chose to suffer
on the rack, to atone.

03:25.881 --> 03:27.048
I hope it works for him.

03:27.082 --> 03:28.883
I hope it makes him right
with his god.

03:28.918 --> 03:32.053
I hope his god shoves a giant
lightning bolt up his ass.

03:32.087 --> 03:33.822
[chuckles]
I'm not saying I forgive him.

03:33.856 --> 03:36.090
I'm just saying
that he was brave.

03:36.125 --> 03:37.559
Braver than his wife.

03:37.593 --> 03:39.494
Braver than Berlin?

03:39.528 --> 03:40.929
[sighs]

03:40.963 --> 03:42.764
I don't want
to talk about her.

03:42.798 --> 03:45.500
You two got pretty close
while I was gone.

03:45.534 --> 03:48.236
I just expected
more from her.

03:48.270 --> 03:51.039
When the E-Rep fell apart,
she was lost.

03:51.073 --> 03:52.707
I gave her a badge.
I let her into my life.

03:52.741 --> 03:54.442
I treated her
like a sister.

03:54.476 --> 03:55.743
Well, that was
your first mistake.

03:55.778 --> 03:57.779
Kenya would have never run.

04:01.317 --> 04:03.218
[panicked chatter]

04:03.252 --> 04:05.220
[gunfire]

04:20.190 --> 04:21.935
Drop the weapon, Lawkeeper.

04:21.970 --> 04:24.973
Eject the mag,
and slide the gun over.

04:25.007 --> 04:26.700
They're gonna kill us anyway.
Just shoot him.

04:26.735 --> 04:29.878
Shoot through me if you have to.

04:29.912 --> 04:32.555
They're wearing body armor.
Wouldn't work.

04:35.667 --> 04:38.553
Votans, stay in the back.

04:38.587 --> 04:41.222
Humans, on your knees
behind the bar,

04:41.257 --> 04:43.925
fingers interlaced
behind your head.

04:43.959 --> 04:46.861
Move! Faster!

04:54.803 --> 04:57.338
We have an important message
for you all.

04:58.974 --> 05:01.976
[device beeps and whirs]

05:04.434 --> 05:06.929
People of Defiance,
as you no doubt know,

05:06.979 --> 05:10.397
I am General Rahm Tak
of the Votanis Collective.

05:11.553 --> 05:12.887
Sorry about the mess,

05:12.922 --> 05:16.424
but I need Mayor Amanda
to understand that I am serious.

05:16.458 --> 05:19.260
Do you understand
that I'm serious?

05:19.295 --> 05:22.497
Can you see me?

05:22.531 --> 05:25.033
Age of miracles, huh?

05:25.067 --> 05:26.434
I have a proposition
for you, Amanda,

05:26.468 --> 05:29.203
and I wish to make it
in front of witnesses.

05:29.238 --> 05:32.407
The war is over.

05:32.441 --> 05:34.008
The humans lost.

05:34.043 --> 05:38.613
The Butcher of Yosemite lost.

05:38.647 --> 05:41.249
My demands are simple:

05:41.283 --> 05:42.483
drop the stasis nets.

05:42.518 --> 05:44.185
Let me in.

05:44.219 --> 05:47.155
In return,
I will allow the humans

05:47.189 --> 05:50.792
safe passage
to find a new home.

05:52.261 --> 05:54.662
You're lying.

05:54.697 --> 05:57.665
If I drop the nets and send
the humans through Bissel Pass,

05:57.700 --> 05:59.667
you will pick them off
like a turkey shoot.

05:59.702 --> 06:01.769
Ah, I would love
nothing more

06:01.804 --> 06:04.672
than to get all the pink-meats
into one spot,

06:04.707 --> 06:08.543
and pew-pew-pew.

06:09.611 --> 06:10.778
But I won't.

06:10.813 --> 06:14.148
- Why not?
- Because I'm a rational man.

06:14.183 --> 06:17.919
A bloodless coup protects
the lives of my soldiers

06:17.953 --> 06:21.556
and keeps you from setting
this town on fire to spite me.

06:21.590 --> 06:23.391
You plan to live here?

06:23.425 --> 06:24.892
It's the perfect home base

06:24.927 --> 06:26.561
with the perfect
security measures.

06:26.595 --> 06:29.731
After you've left,
I will turn Defiance Valley

06:29.765 --> 06:32.900
into a training camp where
no one will dare oppose me.

06:32.935 --> 06:38.039
If the price of that is setting
some humans free, then so be it.

06:38.073 --> 06:40.808
Half of you will die
in the Badlands

06:40.843 --> 06:44.078
without me lifting a finger.

06:44.113 --> 06:48.753
So it's either that,
or the humans die one by one.

06:49.551 --> 06:51.919
- [gunshot]
- [all scream]

06:57.426 --> 06:58.556
So what do you say?

06:58.591 --> 07:00.258
It's the best deal
you're gonna get.

07:00.293 --> 07:02.764
We will fight you
to the bitter end.

07:02.798 --> 07:04.465
We may not win,

07:04.500 --> 07:08.736
but we will make your victory
an unbelievably costly one.

07:08.771 --> 07:11.105
I just hope you have the balls
to show up,

07:11.140 --> 07:12.740
so I can shoot them off.

07:12.775 --> 07:16.295
[laughs]
Funny joke.

07:17.746 --> 07:19.547
- Shoot the hostages.
- No!

07:19.581 --> 07:22.583
[gunfire]

07:24.450 --> 07:25.653
Shoot him!

07:38.880 --> 07:40.835
Nice shooting, Tex.

07:43.672 --> 07:46.641
[dramatic music]

07:46.675 --> 07:54.682
♪ ♪

07:56.946 --> 08:01.946
Sync and corrections by explosiveskull
www.addic7ed.com

08:06.562 --> 08:08.796
Kindzi?

08:08.831 --> 08:11.032
Are you here?

08:11.066 --> 08:14.168
We both know your father
showed poor judgment

08:14.203 --> 08:17.038
by strangling you.

08:17.072 --> 08:19.640
That much is clear.

08:19.675 --> 08:20.675
[gasps]

08:40.263 --> 08:44.665
I'd love the opportunity to

08:44.700 --> 08:47.235
ask him to apologize.

08:53.464 --> 08:56.777
I'd like to apologize as well.

09:09.591 --> 09:11.692
[gasps]

09:18.033 --> 09:21.002
[suspenseful music]

09:21.036 --> 09:29.043
♪ ♪

09:36.265 --> 09:38.942
How did they get
through the stasis nets?

09:38.977 --> 09:41.856
No idea.

09:41.890 --> 09:45.506
But we have to be better.

09:45.541 --> 09:47.962
Hey, Tex.

09:47.996 --> 09:50.164
- You're good in a fight.
- Thanks.

09:50.199 --> 09:53.601
- Got a name?
- Christopher Beckman.

09:53.635 --> 09:56.671
Appreciate the assist.
Where you from?

09:56.705 --> 10:00.741
I'm just heading south
looking for mercenary work.

10:00.776 --> 10:03.010
I ran security
for an APS transport,

10:03.045 --> 10:05.279
smuggling cargo
across the Shipton Desert.

10:05.314 --> 10:06.280
That's a rough haul.

10:06.315 --> 10:07.582
[chuckles]

10:07.616 --> 10:09.584
It's not for the faint of heart,
I can tell you that.

10:09.618 --> 10:12.386
Look, I'm just gonna come out
and say this.

10:12.421 --> 10:13.588
I know this isn't your fight,
but...

10:13.622 --> 10:15.690
You don't have to convince me.

10:15.724 --> 10:18.759
What happened here,
it was wrong.

10:18.794 --> 10:20.595
These people deserve justice.

10:21.663 --> 10:24.198
You can count me in.

10:24.233 --> 10:26.200
Thank you.

10:26.235 --> 10:28.703
Alak, get the militia together,

10:28.737 --> 10:29.770
get them gathered
in Darby Square

10:29.805 --> 10:30.771
in the next 20 minutes.

10:30.806 --> 10:32.173
We're going hunting.

10:32.207 --> 10:34.442
Come on, kid.
Let's get moving.

10:34.476 --> 10:35.776
Yeah, right, sorry.

10:35.811 --> 10:39.113
Show Beckman around,
make sure he's geared up.

10:39.147 --> 10:41.382
Hey. I'm Alak.

10:41.416 --> 10:43.117
Beckman.

10:44.853 --> 10:46.921
Have we met before?

10:46.955 --> 10:48.623
Not that I know of,

10:48.657 --> 10:53.594
but I guess us humans
all look alike to you, huh?

10:53.629 --> 10:55.630
No, that's not what I meant.

10:55.664 --> 10:58.799
Relax, kid,
I'm just having fun.

10:58.834 --> 11:00.835
Let's go meet this militia
of yours.

11:09.544 --> 11:11.545
I heard.

11:13.744 --> 11:16.310
What do you want to do?

11:16.345 --> 11:19.313
I want to fight.
I have to.

11:19.348 --> 11:22.550
What if you panic,
freeze up again?

11:23.466 --> 11:25.986
I won't.

11:26.021 --> 11:27.688
I should have killed Rahm
when I had a chance.

11:27.723 --> 11:28.856
It would have changed
everything.

11:28.890 --> 11:31.058
Look, about that,

11:31.093 --> 11:33.861
I think I rode you
pretty hard.

11:33.895 --> 11:37.298
I never took into account
your feelings about New York,

11:37.332 --> 11:39.700
Tommy.

11:39.735 --> 11:41.235
I guess what I'm trying to say

11:41.269 --> 11:44.171
is that as a father,
I've had better moments.

11:44.206 --> 11:46.674
Did you actually
just apologize?

11:49.111 --> 11:53.681
Let's just put it down to me
getting soft in my old age.

11:53.715 --> 11:57.785
Militia's assembling
in Darby Square.

11:57.819 --> 11:59.820
Why don't you get your ass
down there and report?

12:02.424 --> 12:04.325
And, kiddo?

12:06.328 --> 12:08.028
You didn't give up.

12:08.063 --> 12:09.730
I'm proud of you.

12:14.936 --> 12:18.439
[door opens and closes]

12:18.473 --> 12:20.408
Citizens of Defiance,

12:20.442 --> 12:21.976
as you've probably heard,

12:22.010 --> 12:25.479
this morning our town
was attacked by V.C. terrorists.

12:25.514 --> 12:27.448
Both gunmen were killed.

12:27.482 --> 12:30.518
Tragically, so were
ten innocent citizens.

12:30.552 --> 12:31.819
People you may know.

12:31.853 --> 12:35.856
Friends, parents,
siblings, spouses.

12:35.891 --> 12:38.125
We don't know how the gunmen
entered our town...

12:38.160 --> 12:39.927
Let's go!

12:39.961 --> 12:42.763
(Amanda) Or how many are currently hiding
among us.

12:42.798 --> 12:47.168
At this moment, Lawkeeper Nolan
is organizing a manhunt

12:47.202 --> 12:52.506
to identify and neutralize the
Votanis Collective infiltrators.

12:52.541 --> 12:54.241
Citizens...

12:54.276 --> 12:56.644
We're not really open, sir.

12:56.678 --> 12:58.946
- I'm hungry.
- Haven't you heard?

12:58.980 --> 13:01.582
The V.C. shot up
the NeedWant.

13:01.616 --> 13:04.318
Pancakes, I think.
With fruit.

13:04.352 --> 13:07.455
(Amanda)
At risk of being destroyed.

13:07.489 --> 13:11.692
As the lawkeeper's militia is
searching for these criminals,

13:11.726 --> 13:14.662
I need the streets clear.

13:14.696 --> 13:18.599
I am issuing a mandatory
lockdown for the entire town.

13:18.633 --> 13:21.769
If you are home,
please stay there.

13:21.803 --> 13:25.005
If you are out, you need to get
yourself to the nearest building

13:25.040 --> 13:26.607
and stay indoors

13:26.641 --> 13:29.910
until I announce it's safe
to venture outside again.

13:29.945 --> 13:31.946
This is for your own protection.

13:31.980 --> 13:35.015
It will ensure that you
are not hit by friendly fire

13:35.050 --> 13:37.985
and will aid our militia
in seizing our enemies.

13:39.187 --> 13:40.154
No, no!

13:40.188 --> 13:42.656
[gunfire]

13:44.392 --> 13:46.360
- The shots came from that way.
- All right, you, with me.

13:46.394 --> 13:49.463
- Let's go.
- [gunfire]

13:49.498 --> 13:52.566
That came from Carter Street.
You two, go.

13:52.601 --> 13:53.701
Come on.

13:54.803 --> 13:56.737
[gasps]

14:01.541 --> 14:04.075
_

14:08.034 --> 14:10.368
_

14:10.752 --> 14:12.953
[growling]

14:12.988 --> 14:15.289
[screaming]

14:27.536 --> 14:30.037
Are you gonna kill us?

14:30.071 --> 14:31.705
No.

14:32.777 --> 14:34.644
But the stories...

14:37.069 --> 14:40.614
Old stories.

14:40.649 --> 14:43.083
You're safe now.

14:43.118 --> 14:45.486
Thank you, Omec.

14:45.520 --> 14:48.055
You saved my children.

14:55.228 --> 14:59.046
You did that
with your teeth?

14:59.081 --> 15:02.499
I had no other weapon.

15:02.534 --> 15:05.506
You did good here.
You could do more.

15:11.012 --> 15:12.513
I told you already.

15:12.547 --> 15:16.116
We need you.

15:16.151 --> 15:18.519
This is not my fight.

15:40.833 --> 15:42.567
Kindzi?

16:13.108 --> 16:15.476
<i>Nefkitso.</i>

16:30.191 --> 16:33.627
This is our family.

16:33.662 --> 16:34.895
I wanted you to see them.

16:34.929 --> 16:38.599
Once we have re-powered
our ship, we will wake them up.

16:38.633 --> 16:42.603
Do you want to know
what will happen after that?

16:42.637 --> 16:47.708
We will conquer the Earth
and enslave you all,

16:47.742 --> 16:50.344
do with you what we wish,

16:50.378 --> 16:52.413
feed upon your delicate flesh

16:52.447 --> 16:54.815
on a glorious Dread Harvest.

16:54.849 --> 16:57.651
Why are you telling me
all of this?

16:57.686 --> 16:59.653
Now that you know our secrets,

16:59.688 --> 17:02.775
my father will be forced
to kill you.

17:09.297 --> 17:10.597
[clicking]

17:10.632 --> 17:13.133
[gasps and grunts]

17:19.055 --> 17:20.540
What did she see?

17:20.575 --> 17:23.410
_

17:23.444 --> 17:27.991
_

17:28.025 --> 17:31.002
_

17:36.224 --> 17:37.691
Is it true?

17:37.725 --> 17:39.550
_

17:39.585 --> 17:43.496
_

17:43.531 --> 17:45.165
I have lost one home planet,

17:45.200 --> 17:47.801
and I will be thrice-damned
before I lose another.

17:47.835 --> 17:49.002
_

17:49.003 --> 17:50.237
Is it true?

17:50.271 --> 17:52.884
_

17:54.476 --> 17:56.577
For a time,
I intended to take this planet

17:56.611 --> 17:59.346
and claim it for our people.

17:59.380 --> 18:00.547
And now?

18:02.350 --> 18:06.386
I have seen many things
in Defiance and its people.

18:06.421 --> 18:08.455
Things that I admire.

18:12.527 --> 18:17.265
Our path has changed
to one of inclusion.

18:22.631 --> 18:25.607
_

18:37.752 --> 18:40.721
She is dangerous.

18:43.124 --> 18:47.895
Kindzi will never
accept peace.

18:47.929 --> 18:51.698
If you truly desire an accord
with the people of Earth,

18:51.733 --> 18:53.300
she must be stopped.

18:53.334 --> 18:55.035
Stopped how?

18:55.069 --> 18:58.605
That is not for me to say,

18:58.640 --> 19:01.241
but it does need to happen.

19:04.666 --> 19:08.816
I am fond of you, Stahma,

19:08.850 --> 19:11.385
but we are not a team.

19:11.419 --> 19:14.755
You are not Omec.

19:14.789 --> 19:16.790
Don't ever threaten
my daughter.

19:20.128 --> 19:21.762
I shame myself.

19:21.796 --> 19:25.065
False Casti humility
does not suit you.

19:26.768 --> 19:29.436
Nor does willful ignorance
suit you.

19:30.538 --> 19:33.774
I think we should
both aim higher.

19:35.176 --> 19:38.579
Tread lightly,
little Castithan.

19:38.613 --> 19:41.915
Tread lightly.

19:47.488 --> 19:49.923
[sighs]

19:52.453 --> 19:53.900
Did he say anything?

19:53.935 --> 19:56.211
Anything that might help us
find their accomplices?

19:56.245 --> 19:57.679
The Omec said that
we would be safe now.

19:57.714 --> 19:59.514
Is that true?

19:59.549 --> 20:00.615
Course it is.

20:00.650 --> 20:03.285
You're gonna be just fine.

20:03.319 --> 20:05.053
Found something.

20:11.918 --> 20:13.886
Was in his coat.

20:18.388 --> 20:20.035
What is it?

20:20.069 --> 20:24.006
It's a map of the town.

20:24.040 --> 20:25.941
They didn't come in
over the mountain.

20:25.975 --> 20:28.677
They tunneled in.

20:28.711 --> 20:30.746
(Nolan)
All right.

20:30.780 --> 20:33.148
Alpha team
moves in from the west,

20:33.182 --> 20:34.916
hits that camp with M-19s,

20:34.951 --> 20:37.652
and smokes Rahm's troops
south by southwest

20:37.687 --> 20:38.887
towards the tree line
and the snipers.

20:38.921 --> 20:39.888
What do we got?

20:39.922 --> 20:40.922
Me and Zero on the ridge,

20:40.957 --> 20:42.357
rest of Baker
along the tree line.

20:42.392 --> 20:44.993
- Good job.
- Stop. I've heard enough. No.

20:45.028 --> 20:45.733
No?

20:45.768 --> 20:48.463
No, I want this tunnel sealed up
from this side.

20:48.498 --> 20:49.931
We'll hunt down
whoever's left in town,

20:49.966 --> 20:52.501
and we'll live to fight
another day.

20:52.535 --> 20:55.303
We're badly outnumbered.

20:55.338 --> 20:58.073
This is our chance
to take the fight to him,

20:58.107 --> 21:00.475
to take him by surprise.

21:00.510 --> 21:03.145
[hailer chirps]

21:03.179 --> 21:04.713
Alak.
What do you got?

21:04.747 --> 21:07.716
It's 2, maybe 3 miles long.

21:07.750 --> 21:09.084
It's all clear out here.

21:09.118 --> 21:10.452
(Nolan) Nothing suspicious?
No booby traps?

21:10.486 --> 21:12.587
- I'm still in one piece.
- All right.

21:12.622 --> 21:14.723
I want you to lay up somewhere
safe, keep your eyes open.

21:14.757 --> 21:17.459
You spot any V.C.,
chirp me a warning.

21:17.493 --> 21:18.827
Will do.

21:18.861 --> 21:20.796
- And, Alak?
- Yeah?

21:20.830 --> 21:24.466
Took guts to volunteer.
Good job.

21:24.500 --> 21:27.369
Thanks.

21:27.403 --> 21:29.704
This is the closest thing
to a guarantee we're gonna get.

21:29.739 --> 21:31.393
No, it's a huge risk.

21:31.428 --> 21:34.409
So was crossing the Delaware,
but Washington was game.

21:36.045 --> 21:37.446
[sighs]

21:39.282 --> 21:41.249
- All right, do it.
- All right.

21:41.284 --> 21:42.784
Bring that son of a bitch down.

21:42.819 --> 21:45.639
All right, Beckman, you're
up front with me and Irisa.

21:45.674 --> 21:49.658
Zero and Dell, Barnes are next
and my three EMC guys.

21:49.692 --> 21:53.361
After that, we're gonna go
with squads one through four.

21:53.396 --> 21:55.030
Amanda, you're gonna take
the remainder of the troops.

21:55.064 --> 21:56.164
You're gonna surround
the building.

21:56.199 --> 21:57.432
Nobody gets in or out.

21:57.467 --> 21:59.000
- Anything suspicious at all...
- Chirp your hailer.

21:59.035 --> 22:01.937
Good luck.

22:01.971 --> 22:04.272
Okay, everybody, bring it in.

22:04.307 --> 22:06.942
No. I don't want him in there.

22:06.976 --> 22:07.943
It's not your choice.

22:07.977 --> 22:10.212
You're staying with me.

22:11.198 --> 22:12.999
I'm going.

22:18.621 --> 22:20.589
Just be careful.

22:20.623 --> 22:21.623
Always.

22:31.206 --> 22:35.437
All right, everybody.
Come on in.

22:35.471 --> 22:37.606
We get down there,
stay alert.

22:37.640 --> 22:39.005
Check your equipment
then check the equipment

22:39.040 --> 22:40.742
of the trooper next to you.

22:40.776 --> 22:44.045
We're gonna be moving in fours,
so we want clear lines of fire.

22:44.080 --> 22:45.647
We're gonna move slowly,

22:45.681 --> 22:48.650
we're gonna move by the numbers,
and safely.

22:48.684 --> 22:50.018
And remember,

22:50.052 --> 22:52.654
I chose each and every one
of you for a reason.

22:52.688 --> 22:57.692
Together, we're gonna
make Defiance proud.

22:57.727 --> 22:59.628
All right, let's line 'em up.

22:59.662 --> 23:01.163
Move out.

23:14.944 --> 23:16.347
[gasps]

23:16.382 --> 23:19.080
Sorry, sorry.

23:19.902 --> 23:22.284
This is all new to me.

23:22.318 --> 23:24.186
Keep it down.

23:25.388 --> 23:26.488
It's okay.

23:31.494 --> 23:34.462
[dramatic music]

23:34.497 --> 23:42.504
♪ ♪

24:06.854 --> 24:09.631
Everyone, hold position here
until you get my signal.

24:09.665 --> 24:12.067
You're with me.

24:12.101 --> 24:20.108
♪ ♪

24:32.479 --> 24:33.989
Go.

24:34.023 --> 24:42.030
