You just gonna stand there?

29:08.352 --> 29:10.142
Amanda was right.

29:10.177 --> 29:11.751
If we had just blown
our end of the tunnel,

29:11.786 --> 29:13.122
they'd all still be alive.

29:13.157 --> 29:14.257
You gambled.

29:14.291 --> 29:16.611
If it had worked,
you'd be a hero.

29:16.646 --> 29:20.129
Yeah, but it didn't,
so what does that make me?

29:20.164 --> 29:22.014
They trusted me,
they followed me,

29:22.049 --> 29:23.750
and now they're dead
because of me.

29:23.785 --> 29:27.288
You didn't kill them.
Rahm Tak did.

29:27.323 --> 29:29.105
You can carry that weight
on your shoulders,

29:29.140 --> 29:32.408
but it doesn't make it right.

29:32.443 --> 29:36.212
That's what you've been
telling me all along, right?

29:36.247 --> 29:38.915
Nice try, kid.

29:38.949 --> 29:41.217
You get yourself some rest.

29:41.252 --> 29:43.353
Nolan, we've got trouble.

29:43.387 --> 29:44.458
What is it?

29:44.493 --> 29:46.589
Rahm Tak is setting up camp
right outside the stasis nets.

29:46.624 --> 29:48.124
He's trying to squeeze us.

29:48.158 --> 29:49.192
It's a blockade.

29:49.226 --> 29:51.794
I've got an idea.

29:51.829 --> 29:52.796
Speak.

29:52.831 --> 29:57.433
If it works, it's a surefire way
to destroy Rahm and his army.

29:57.468 --> 29:58.968
But there's a catch.

29:59.003 --> 30:00.103
What?

30:00.137 --> 30:03.706
It's a suicide mission.

30:03.741 --> 30:05.272
Still listening.

30:05.307 --> 30:08.125
A stasis net is comprised
of tenser particles.

30:08.160 --> 30:09.414
When chained together,
they're stable

30:09.449 --> 30:11.542
and can form
an impenetrable barrier.

30:11.577 --> 30:14.506
If you use a device to reverse
the electromagnetic charge,

30:14.541 --> 30:17.152
the tenser particles
unhook and explode.

30:17.187 --> 30:18.683
Same principle used
in the net cutter.

30:18.718 --> 30:20.884
Gold star for cowboy guy.

30:20.919 --> 30:23.493
Rahm Tak has done us
an enormous favor

30:23.527 --> 30:26.689
by setting up his camp
next to a gigantic bomb.

30:26.724 --> 30:29.701
If we can contain and focus
the force of the explosion...

30:29.736 --> 30:33.169
say, using a localized
singularity field, then...

30:33.203 --> 30:34.279
We can blow him to hell.

30:34.314 --> 30:36.352
And you get a sticker
that says "teacher's pet."

30:36.387 --> 30:39.042
See me after class.

30:39.076 --> 30:41.677
I can throw together
a targeting device.

30:41.712 --> 30:44.647
It's small,
so I can surgically implant it

30:44.682 --> 30:46.399
into the volunteer's forearm.

30:46.434 --> 30:47.972
Into my forearm.

30:48.007 --> 30:51.000
It's nonmetallic, and it will
be invisible to the scanners.

30:51.035 --> 30:53.368
So you'll talk your way
into Rahm Tak's camp,

30:53.403 --> 30:55.692
and when you're dead center,

30:55.726 --> 30:57.646
I'll blow the nets remotely.

30:57.681 --> 30:59.996
Bye-bye, Rahm Tak.
Bye-bye, Army.

31:00.030 --> 31:02.565
And bye-bye, Nolan.
Unacceptable.

31:02.600 --> 31:04.033
- It's necessary.
- No.

31:04.068 --> 31:05.969
I'm not letting you
throw your life away.

31:06.003 --> 31:07.333
If this plan fails,

31:07.368 --> 31:09.839
I need you alive to decide
whatever plan B is.

31:09.873 --> 31:11.174
There is no plan B.

31:11.208 --> 31:13.760
There's always a plan B.

31:13.795 --> 31:15.278
You know,
put the gizmo in my arm.

31:15.312 --> 31:16.186
- (both) No.
- Yes.

31:16.221 --> 31:17.480
If it fails,
I become a martyr.

31:17.514 --> 31:18.481
You can use it to bring
humans and Votans together.

31:18.515 --> 31:20.016
That's the most
ridiculous idea.

31:20.050 --> 31:21.017
- No, we're not doing it.
- I'm not arguing about this.

31:21.051 --> 31:23.938
You guys are
ignoring the obvious.

31:23.973 --> 31:25.188
You should be resting.

31:25.222 --> 31:26.897
Rahm Tak
knows we're desperate.

31:26.932 --> 31:28.691
He's expecting a trick.

31:28.726 --> 31:30.093
The minute he sees
either of you coming,

31:30.127 --> 31:33.329
he'll have a sniper pick you off
from half a mile away.

31:33.364 --> 31:35.398
And who do you think
can get close enough?

31:36.064 --> 31:38.558
Only one person I know of.

