33:39.074 --> 33:40.274
Alak and your grandson

33:40.309 --> 33:42.227
have to bear the burden
of the Tarr family name

33:42.262 --> 33:44.278
for the rest of their lives.

33:44.313 --> 33:47.115
Why are you here?

33:48.650 --> 33:52.019
I'm offering you
a chance at redemption.

33:52.054 --> 33:53.921
And Stahma?

33:53.956 --> 33:56.058
She's still missing.

33:56.093 --> 33:58.326
But if she turns up alive,

33:58.360 --> 34:02.096
I will pardon her crimes,
as I will pardon yours.

34:03.283 --> 34:04.432
Posthumously.

34:04.466 --> 34:09.137
Ah, there's the catch.

34:10.877 --> 34:16.101
Rahm Tak's men
shot Alak.

34:16.137 --> 34:17.915
We almost lost him.

34:17.949 --> 34:22.079
Now, I'm giving you a chance
to kill Rahm Tak,

34:22.114 --> 34:23.523
a chance to save Defiance,

34:23.565 --> 34:27.493
a chance to save your son
and your grandson.

34:29.639 --> 34:31.241
Will you help us?

34:41.904 --> 34:45.005
I could not be prouder
of you.

34:49.603 --> 34:53.547
I hope I can live up
to your example.

35:01.134 --> 35:04.148
I've seen all I need to.

35:04.183 --> 35:06.160
Let's go.

35:24.394 --> 35:25.870
He's through.

35:25.905 --> 35:27.606
Re-engage the nets.

35:29.608 --> 35:32.986
[device humming]

35:39.528 --> 35:41.295
Someone's heading this way.

35:41.330 --> 35:43.446
(Rahm)
Shoot 'em in the head.

35:43.481 --> 35:46.078
I think it's Datak Tarr.

35:46.113 --> 35:49.036
What? No.

35:58.456 --> 36:01.282
Should we take him out?

36:01.317 --> 36:03.651
Uh-uh.

36:03.685 --> 36:06.020
He's got me curious.

36:07.416 --> 36:10.384
[dramatic music]

36:10.419 --> 36:17.325
